    "title": "Frontier: Future of AI and Blockchain",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "ml_patterns",
        "title": "AI Network ML Patterns",
        "content": "## Realizing Distributed Machine Learning\n\nThe AI Network architecture paper presents methods for implementing various machine learning patterns in a distributed environment.\n\n### 1. Distributed Computing\n\n> \"Decompose tasks into small pieces, send asynchronously\"\n\n```\nLarge task\n    ↓\nDecompose into small chunks\n    ↓\nDistribute to multiple Workers\n    ↓\nCollect & synthesize results\n```\n\n**Use cases**:\n- Large-scale data preprocessing\n- Distributed inference (run multiple models in parallel)\n- Batch processing\n\n### 2. Optimizing Loss Function\n\n> \"Workers compete to achieve L(w) → 0\"\n\n```\nClient: Define objective function L(w)\n    ↓\nWorkers: Each attempts optimization\n    ↓\nEvaluator: Select lowest loss achiever\n    ↓\nDistribute rewards\n```\n\n**Use cases**:\n- Hyperparameter tuning\n- AutoML experiments\n- Neural Architecture Search (NAS)\n\n### 3. Data Parallelism\n\n> \"Client acts as parameter server\"\n\n```\n        Parameter Server (Client)\n         ↑ Gradients  ↓ Parameters\n    ┌────┼────────────┼────┐\n    ↓    ↓            ↓    ↓\n Worker1 Worker2   Worker3 Worker4\n (Data1) (Data2)  (Data3) (Data4)\n```\n\n**Use cases**:\n- Large model training\n- Distributed fine-tuning\n\n### 4. Reinforcement Training\n\n> \"AlphaGo case: share self-play data\"\n\n```\n       Environment (Game Server)\n             ↓ State\n    ┌────────┼────────┐\n    ↓        ↓        ↓\n Agent1   Agent2   Agent3\n    │        │        │\n    └────────┼────────┘\n             ↓\n      Experience Pool\n             ↓\n      Central Model Update\n```\n\n**Use cases**:\n- Game AI training\n- Robot simulation\n- Autonomous driving scenario learning\n\n### Analogy: Research Lab Network\n\nLike research labs around the world collaborating:\n- Each lab = Worker\n- Research topic = Task\n- Paper publication = Result submission\n- Peer review = Evaluator\n\n### Practical Implementation Considerations\n\n- **Communication overhead**: Gradient compression needed\n- **Asynchronous updates**: Stale gradient problem\n- **Privacy**: Federated Learning techniques applicable",
        "position": {
          "x": 7,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "open_resource",
        "title": "Open Source to Open Resource",
        "content": "## From Static Code to Living Agents\n\nCore vision of AI Network's 2025 whitepaper: **Open Resource**.\n\n### Limitations of Open Source\n\n**Execution Gap**:\n> \"Open source AI cannot run in typical environments\"\n\n```\nMeta releases LLaMA\n    ↓\nCode is on GitHub but...\n    ↓\nTo run: 8x A100 GPUs, hundreds of GB RAM\n    ↓\nRegular developers cannot use it\n```\n\n### Value Centralization Problem\n\n> \"Platforms like ChatGPT don't return value to original creators\"\n\n- Trained on open source models/data\n- Commercial value monopolized by platforms\n- No rewards to original authors\n\n### Open Resource's Solution\n\n```\nOpen Source          →      Open Resource\n─────────────────────────────────────────\nStatic code                 Living agents\nExecution on your own       Network provides execution\nFree but requires resources Token access to resources\nHard to track contributions On-chain contribution records\n```\n\n### Sovereign Agent\n\n> \"AI agent operating autonomously on-chain\"\n\n- Has own wallet\n- Executes transactions autonomously\n- Distributes revenue to creators/contributors\n\n```\nUser request → AI Agent → Provide service\n                  ↓\n            Revenue generated\n                  ↓\n        ┌────────┼────────┐\n        ↓        ↓        ↓\n   Model author  Data provider  Infra provider\n```\n\n### True Promise of World Computer\n\n> \"Living network of cooperating intelligences\"\n\nEthereum proposed 'World Computer' but:\n- Actually only simple logic possible\n- Unsuitable for AI workloads\n\nAI Network's vision:\n- True World Computer capable of distributed AI execution\n- Open source AI truly existing as 'alive'\n\n### Analogy: Orchestra\n\n- **Open Source** = Sheet music (anyone can see, but needs instruments and musicians)\n- **Open Resource** = Sheet music + Orchestra network (request performance anytime)\n\nSheet music alone won't let you hear music, but with an orchestra network, you can request a performance anytime.\n\n### Future Outlook\n\n- Agent-to-Agent collaboration\n- Autonomous value creation and distribution\n- Decentralized AI service marketplace",
        "position": {
          "x": 11,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
